--50.) What if you try to promote a piece onto a square that uses its own (old) position as a base?
doMove Play at [1,1]
doMove Play at [1,2]
doMove Play at [2,1]
doMove Play at [2,2]
doMove Promote from [1,1] to [1,1]
doMove Promote from [2,1] to [1,1]
showBoard

--51.) What if I try and promote a piece *down* a level instead of *up* a level?
undoLastMove 1000
doMove Play at [0,1]
doMove Play at [0,2]
doMove Play at [1,1]
doMove Play at [1,2]
doMove Play at [2,0]
doMove Play at [0,3]
doMove Play at [2,1]
doMove Play at [0,1]
doMove Promote from [0,1] to [3,3]

--52.) What if I try and promote a piece, but promote it parallel?
undoLastMove 1000
doMove Play at [0,1]
doMove Play at [0,2]
doMove Play at [1,1]
doMove Play at [1,2]
doMove Play at [2,0]
doMove Play at [0,3]
doMove Play at [2,1]
doMove Play at [2,2]
doMove Promote from [0,2] to [0,1]
doMove Play at [3,3]
doMove Promote from [0,1] to [1,1]
showBoard

--53.) Can you remove a sphere out of the square that is used to get the square bonus?
undoLastMove 1000
doMove Play at [0,0]
doMove Play at [2,2]
doMove Play at [0,1]
doMove Play at [2,3]
doMove Play at [1,0]
doMove Play at [3,2]
showBoard
doMove Play at [0, 2]                          
undoLastMove 1
doMove Play at [0, 3]                         
undoLastMove 1
doMove Play at [1, 1]                          
undoLastMove 1
doMove Play at [1, 1] taking [0, 0]           
undoLastMove 1
doMove Play at [1, 1] taking [0, 0] and [0, 1] 
undoLastMove 1
doMove Play at [1, 1] taking [0, 0] and [1, 0]
undoLastMove 1
doMove Play at [1, 1] taking [1, 1]
undoLastMove 1

--54.) Can you remove a sphere out of the square that is used to get the square bonus, even if it's supporting another sphere?
undoLastMove 1000
