--56.) If you yank a sphere from the bottom row to move it up to the top, can you place a sphere on the square of spheres that it used to help create?
doMove Play at [0,0]
doMove Play at [1,0]
doMove Play at [1,1]
showBoard
doMove Promote from [0,3] to [0,0]
doMove Play at [0,2]
showBoard

--57.) Make sure that you can't make an alignment over different levels.  E.g. WWBW, but the [0,2] on the second row is W, making [0,0], [0,1], [0,2] and [0,3] White.
undoLastMove 1000
doMove Play at [0,0]
doMove Play at [1,0]
doMove Play at [0,1]
doMove Play at [1,1]
doMove Play at [1,2]
doMove Play at [0,2]
doMove Play at [0,3]
doMove Play at [0,0]
doMove Play at [3,3]
doMove Play at [1,3]
doMove Play at [0,2] taking [3,3]
doMove Play at [0,2] taking [0,2] and [3,3]



